<br>
Bad quests = the Jboots quest....the epitomy of bad quest design <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Remfin<BR>
Level 60 Sorceror<BR>
Terris - Thule<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaneric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daneric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 3:23:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are Quests Fun? (not a rant!)</span><hr size=1> I too love quests. All the Sol Ro items when that zone opened. It really helped my wizard. I wore the Acumen mask for god knows how many levels (50+). And now I carry it once again for an instant recast item (it too does not need to be equipped to use) for those mobs that require it (Dozekar). Flux Staff? Still hotkeyed like most every wizard. It has been my friend for going on 2 years. Runescale cloak? Still carry it for DR/PR gear.<br>
<br>
7th Shawl. Most cherished possession because I made it myself and put in all my spare time on it. Quest. many parts were fun. Some were not.<br>
<br>
It is Everquest afterall. <br>
<br>
Staff of Wheel? A right of passage for all young wizards. Loved the quest. Died many times acquiring it many moons ago.  I wish they would make a quest involving you to turn this in to someone. It is past its prime for the most part.<br>
<br>
Tumpy Tonics. 2400 of them completely got me from beginning of level 48 to ding! 49 (It was actually faster than hunting I believe and I just couldn't WAIT for Ice Comet) That is where I also became a master brewer (135). Hey I like quests I said!<br>
<br>
Quests are what you make them. If you approach them like work, then they will seem like work. But somehow the reward, no matter how small, is always gratifying for a quest you did.<br>
<br>
And the BEST part of being a wizard is that we can do SO many of them solo (way before other classes can solo them) unlike other classes.<br>
<br>
Daneric<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryzak620.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryzak620</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 11:17:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are Quests Fun? (not a rant!)</span><hr size=1> I am in agreement with most posters here. I enjoy quests immensely, as long as I don't have to sit at a camp forever hoping for a ultra-rare spawn.  One reason I haven't done much for my epic is that 1) I don't have the patience to wait for phinny/vs to pop on their long rotations (I understand why, but it's still ridiculous) 2) I don't belong to an uber guild and will never be able to beat them to these spawns.  Everytime Phinny pops, one of the uber guilds is usually there w/in 5 minutes, and 30 minutes later, Phinny is toast.<br>
<br>
The quests I enjoyed the most were the Temple quests.  SoTF was a truly fun quest, that my friends were able to help me with, and was able to get it in a few hours. At lvl 52, I still have my acumen mask and runescale cloak on me.  Once I get something better, I will replace them, but I have yet to get or buy better.<br>
Staff of Wheel quest was truly great. I did 8/10's of it solo.  And had a cleric friend help me w/ the hand in L guk. we ran to the camp ITU, then he threw up Divine Aura, while i grabbed the rod and evac'ed us.  The other part I did w/ a friend, was the Lake Rathe (I hate that ONE gobbie that sees invis...grrrrrr).  I died several times doing the rathe and oasis one, just cause of those gobbies, but it was worth it.  I did that quest 3 times. 2 times for the runes, and once for the actual staff and identify crystal.  I kept that staff until about a week ago, when some friends got me the sorcerous bowl and book of obulous.  If you are pre-49ish, and turn in the staff and crystal for the runes, you get really, really good exp for them. Plus you have the runes to make Ice Comet!<br>
       Lately, I have found myself doing quests for my twinks (ranger, enchanter, mage), and having a blast doing those too.  My chanter now has most of the incandescent items, and my mage has 3/4 of the focus items.  Quests are a great break from the grind of leveling, and with a wiz, i can farm pretty much every zone in the old world with relative ease. Probably one of the biggest reasons I don't level as quick as others, is that I always need to keep the game fresh for me, so I do a whole bunch of different things just to have fun with the game.<br>
<br>
Ryzak Myrdhyn<br>
52 Channeler<br>
Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6322.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6308.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=6266.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=6266.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6266.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6266.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm27">PVP Forum<option value="gr